wings, nails and beak 1. 28. 19, 20, 22. [Ac-
cording to Nī., name of a Yakṣa, cf. अश्व-
क्रन्दादयो नव यक्षाः on 1. 32. 18 Bom.
Ed.].

प्रलिह
Praliha m.: A mythical bird.
He fought with Garuḍa when the latter
was on his expedition to fetch अमृत; Garuḍa
