wind’ (वातवेग), and ‘having excess of
poison’ (विषोल्बण) 1. 52. 14, 13, 1.

प्रह्लाद
Prahlāda m.: A mythical serpent.
One of the serpents who, without feeling
fatigue (विगतक्लम), wait upon Varuṇa in
his सभा; described as marked with banner
(पताकिन्), round spots (मण्डलिन्), and
