sacrifice of Janamejaya; described as ‘fast as
wind’ (वातवेग) and ‘having excess of
poison’ (वीषोल्बण) 1. 52. 17, 13.

मण्डलक
Maṇḍalaka m.: A mythical serpent.
Born in the कुल of Takṣaka, listed by
Sūta among those who were offered in the
snake sacrifice of Janamejaya 1. 52. 7, 6, 9.

मधुपर्क
Madhuparka m.: A mythical bird,
living in the world of Suparṇas 5. 99. 14, 1.
Born in the कुल of Vainateya (Garuḍa),
in the वंश of Kaśyapa; feeding on serpents;
marked with श्रीवत्स, his deity is Viṣṇu; by
action a Kṣatriya, not obtaining Brahminhood
because engaged in destroying his kinsmen 5.
99. 2-8.

मलय
Malaya m.: A mythical bird, living
in the world of Suparṇas 5. 99. 14, 1.
Born in the कुल of Vainateya (Garuḍa),
in the वंश of Kaśyapa; feeding on serpents;
marked with श्रीवत्स his deity is Viṣṇu; by
action a Kṣatriya, not obtaining Brahmin-
hood because engaged in destroying his kins-
men 5. 99. 2-8.

महाजय
Mahājaya m.: A mythical serpent.
Vāsuki gave two snakes, Jaya and
Mahājaya, to the son of Agni (i. e. Skanda)
9. 44. 48.

महापद्म
Mahāpadma m.: A mythical elephant.
One of the great elephants (महानागस्),
