poison’ (विषोल्बण) 1. 52. 14, 13.

शङ्ख
Śaṅkha m.: A mythical serpent, living
in Bhogavatī Purī 5. 101. 12, 1.
Son of Surasā and Kaśyapa 5. 101. 4,
17; description 5. 101. 5-7; also listed by
Sūta among the sons of Kadrū 1. 31. 8; he
was one of those who received the white
