Son of Śvetā, who was one of the dau-
ghters of Krodhavaśā (or of Tāmrā ? 1. 60.
54); quick in his gait (आशुग) 1. 60. 64.

श्वेता
Śvetā f.: A mythical female elephant (?)
One of the nine daughters of Krodha-
vaśā (or of Tāmrā ? 1. 60. 54; in that case
क्रोधवशा ‘irascible’), she gave birth to the
cardinal elephant Śveta 1. 60. 59, 64.

संवर्तक
Saṃvartaka m.: A mythical serpent.
Son of Kadrū, listed among her sons by
Sūta at the request of Śaunaka 1. 31. 10, 2.

संवृत्त
Saṃvṛtta m.: A mythical serpent,
living in Bhogavatī Purī 5. 101. 14, 1.
Son of Surasā and Kaśyapa 5. 101.
4, 17; description 5. 101. 5-7.

संहताङ्गद
Saṃhatāṅgada m.: A mythical serpent.
Born in the कुल of Airāvata, listed by
Sūta among those offered in the snake sacri-
fice of Janamejaya 1. 52. 10, 11.

सप्तवार
Saptavāra m.: A mythical bird, living
in the world of the Suparṇas 5. 99. 11, 1.
Born in the कुल of Vainateya (Garuḍa),
in the वंश of Kaśyapa; feeding on serpents;
marked with श्रीवत्स, his deity is Viṣṇu; by
