C. Characteristics: (1) Mytho-
logical: (i) Gods assemble on Himavant
(विद्यते हि गिरिश्रेष्ठे त्रिदशानां समा-
गमः) 3. 40. 30; (ii) Four Lokapālas, gods
and sages always come there for the benefit
of the world (चत्वारो लोकपालाश् च देवाः
सर्षिगणास् तथा।यत्र नित्यं समायान्ति
लोकस्य हितकाम्यया) 12. 314. 6; (iii)
Kirāta (Śiva) lives on the summit of Hima-
vant (हिमवच्छिखरालयः) 3. 40. 29;
there is the abode of Rudra on Himavant
(रुद्रस्यायतनम्) which is resorted to by
Siddhas and Cāraṇas, by Pārṣadas, Piśācas
and various forest tribes (वन्यैर् नाना-
विधैस् तथा); they all serve Śarva there
13. 19. 16-18; the place is liked by Śiva and
he is always present there 13. 19. 19; 5. 109.
5; (iv) Gods, Gandharvas and Apsarases
have their playgrounds on many inaccessible
regions of Himavant (गिरेर् अस्य दुर्गान्
देशान् बहून् … ।आक्रीडभूतान् देवानां
गन्धर्वाप्सरसां तथा) 1. 111. 6; (v)
It has Kubera's gardens (उद्यानानि कुबेर-
स्य) 1. 111. 7; (vi) Garutmant, king of
birds, always visits it 12. 314. 6; 2. Inhabi-
tants: (i) Himavant protects Rakṣases and
Piśācas 8. 30. 78; 6. 7. 48; (ii) Kirātas
living there subsist on fruits and roots and
are dressed in skins (फलमूलाशना ये च
कीराताश् चर्मवाससः) 2. 48. 8; they live in
its inaccessible regions (हिमवद्दुर्गनि-
लयाः किराताः) 7. 4. 6; (iii) Mlecchas also
live in its inaccessible regions (हिमवद्दुर्ग-
वासिनो म्लेच्छाः) 7. 87. 37; (iv) A certain
learned Brāhmaṇa, son of Pippalāda and of
Kuśika gotra, lived for long on the summit of
Himavant 12. 192. 5; 3. The righteous people
are reborn there; the unrighteous ones do not
go to the north (इहत्यास् तत्र जायन्ते ये वै
पुण्यकृतो जनाः।असत्कर्माणि कुर्वन्तः
 … इहैव परिवर्तन्ते न ते यान्त्य् उत्तरां
दिशम्) 12. 185. 21-23; 4. The Himavant
region is full of many wonders (बह्वाश्चर्यो
हि देशः सः) 14. 14. 9; (तत्राहम् अद्भुतान्
भावान् अपश्यं गिरिसत्तमे) 13. 14. 27;
3. 141. 25; 5. (a) Āśramas on it of: (i)
Nara and Nārāyaṇa 12. 334. 2; (ii) Vaiyā-
ghrapadya Upamanyu 13. 14. 28 (the आश्रम
is described in 13. 14. 27-44); (iii) Nārada
(हिमवन्तं जगामाशु यत्रास्य स्वक
आश्रमः) 12. 334. 2; (iv) Vṛṣaparvan 3.
155. 17; (b) Other places on it: (i) large
realm of Subāhu (सुबाहोर् विषयं महत्)
3. 141. 24-25; (ii) Muñjapṛṣṭha and
Muñjavant on the summit of Himavant (and
on Meru) 12. 122. 2-3; 14. 8. 1; (iii) Pitā-
mahasaras 3. 82. 128; (iv) A holy and
dirtfree pond of lotuses (हिमवतः पुण्यो
विमलः कमलाकरः) and the forest Jai-
mūta 5. 109. 21-22; 6. Animals, birds and
trees: (i) Elephants of Himavant (हैम-
वता गजेन्द्राः) 1. 178. 2; (नागाः … हैम-
वताः) 4. 49. 15; (हैमवताः … गजाः) 8. 62.
36; (गजौ हैमवतौ) 8. 65. 2; (नागं
प्रभिन्नं गिरिकूटकल्पम् उपत्यकां
हैमवतीं चरन्तम्) 3. 252. 5; (ii) Lions:
Lions from the forests on Himavant (हिम-
वद्वनसंभूतं सिंहं केसरिणम्)
3. 292. 21; (सिंहाः हैमवताः) 2. 19. 25;
2. 68. 15; (iii) Swans: swans in their flight
