(कौरवान् अभ्यभाषत) 13. 154. 19;
Arjuna called the foremost among Kaura-
vas (कौरवाणां धुरंधरे) 14. 78. 36;
Dhṛtarāṣṭra admitted his fault to Kauravas
that he installed Duryodhana as their
chief (ममापराधात् तत् सर्वम् इति ज्ञेयं
तु कौरवाः … दुर्योधनम् कौरवाणाम्
आधिपत्ये ऽभ्यषेचयम्) 15. 5. 1-2; when
Dhṛtarāṣṭra left for the forest, women
of the royal family of Kauravas (कौरव-
राजवंश्याः) uttered loud cry 15. 21. 4; all
Kaurava women made a round of Dhṛta-
rāṣṭra, Gāndhārī and Kuntī (प्रजग्मुस्
ते प्रदक्षिणम्। … सर्वाः कौरवयोषितः)
15. 44. 49.
C. Those present in the
Sabhā of Hāstinapura: 1. The द्यूत-
सभा: Vikarṇa exhorted the Kauravas to
reply to Draupadī's question (विब्रूत॥।
तद् धि वक्ष्यामि कौरवाः) 2. 61. 19;
none of the Kauravyas present in the Sabhā
replied to the question (न विब्रुवन्ति
कौरव्याः प्रश्नम् एतम्) 2. 61. 50; Drau-
padī exhorted the Kauravas present in the
Sabhā to reply to her question 2. 62. 11-
13; Bhīma spoke in the assembly of the
Kauravas (संसदि कौरवाणाम्) 2. 68. 25;
Nārada prophesied that the Kauravas
seated in the assembly would perish in the
coming fourteenth year 2. 71. 30; Karṇa
abused Draupadī (in the Sabhā) in the pre-
sence of all Kauravas 7. 112. 39; citizens
of Hāstinapura grieved when at the end
of the द्यूत in the assembly hall of Kaura-
vas, Pāṇḍavas went out of Hāstinapura
(द्यूते राजन् कौरवाणां सभायाम्) 15. 21.
12; 2. The राजसभा of the Kauravas: 1.
Saṃjaya reminded the Kauravas (present in
the assembly) of their ancient धर्मस्
(एतान् धर्मान् कौरवाणां पुराणान्) 5. 29.
29; Saṃjaya addressed the Kauravas seated
in the Sabhā (5. 46. 2, राजसभा 5. 46. 3)
after his return from the Pāṇḍavas (तद्
विजानीत कौरवाः) 5. 46. 15 (those
present in the Sabhā included Bhīṣma,
Dhṛtarāṣṭra, Vidura, Somadatta, Duryo-
dhana and other sons of Dhṛtarāṣṭra,
and also Droṇa, Kṛpa, Śalya, Kṛtavar-
man, Jayadratha, Aśvatthāman, Śakuni,
Karṇa, Ulūka (5. 46. 3-9); Karṇa
spoke to Duryodhana in the assembly
of Kauravas (संसदि कौरवाणां)
5. 61. 1; Duḥśāsana feared that the
Kauravas might tie up Duryodhana and
hand him over to Yudhiṣṭhira (बद्ध्वा
किल त्वां दास्यन्ति कुन्तीपुत्राय कौरवाः)
5. 126. 22; Karṇa always boasted in the
संसद् of the Kauravas 8. 46. 35.
D.
Although it is difficult always to distinguish
between those born in Kuru family in gene-
ral and the sons of Dhṛtarāṣṭra in parti-
cular, in the following references the terms
Kaurava, Kauraveya and Kauravya (pl.)
