1) were completely destroyed (भरतानां
महाक्षयम्) 9. 2. 62; (52) Scenes on the
battlefield: Some of the women of Bharatas
(Kauravas) stumbled, and some fell
on the ground after visiting the battlefield
(भरतस्त्रियः (कुरुस्त्रियः 11. 16. 10) ।
शरीरेष्व् अस्खलन्न् अन्या न्यपतंश् चापरा
भुवि) 11. 16. 14; some of them (भरत-
योषितः) were not able to recognize their
husbands whose bodies were mutilated 11.
16. 53; (pitiable condition of the widows
described by Gāndhārī 11. 16. 42-58);
