was fortunate in that he was not alive to
witness the terrible destruction of Bharatas
(दारुणं भरतक्षयम्) 11. 24. 4; Gān-
dhārī cursed Kṛṣṇa saying that Yādava
women, with their husbands and relatives
killed, would fall on the ground like the
Bharata women (यथैते भरतस्त्रियः)
11. 25. 42; (53) Bhagavān had told his
son Apāntaratamas (Vyāsa 12. 337. 38, 43)
that when Tiṣya (i. e. Kaliyuga) would
arrive Kurus, called Bhāratas, would be-
come famous kings, but there would be
family feud resulting in mutual destruction
(पुनस् तिष्ये च संप्राप्ते कुरवो नाम
