मधु
Madhu, Mādhava m. (pl.): Name of
a people, one of the Yādavas.
A. Epic events: (1) In fear of Jarā-
sandha, Mādhavas fled to Kuśasthalī in
the west near the Raivata mountain; seeing
the mountain and the Mādhavītīrtha, they
were highly delighted (माधवाः … परां
मुदम् अवाप्नुवन्) 2. 13. 52; (2) Kṛṣṇa
assured Yudhiṣṭhira that the army of the
Madhus consisting of horse-riders, foot-
soldiers, horses, chariots and elephants
and led by Balarāma was at his disposal
( … मधूनाम्।सेना तवार्थेषु नरेन्द्र
यत्ता ससादिपत्त्यश्वरथा सनागा) 3. 180,
32 (Nī. on Bom. Ed. 3. 183. 33: मधूनां
माथुराणाम्। … यत्ता सन्नद्धा); (3)
Arjuna told Vāsudeva that he would be
unable to bear for long the sight of the
earth bereft of Kṛṣṇa and Madhus (नाहं
वृष्णिप्रवीरेण मधुभिश् चैव मातुल।
व्थीनां पृथिवीं द्रष्टुम् शक्तश् चिरम् इह
प्रभो॥) 16. 8. 2.
