वेणिक
Veṇika m. (pl.): Name of a people.
On the second day of the war, Veṇika
warriors with their armies led by Duḥ-
śāsana, Vikarṇa and others were among
those who were expected to protect
Bhīṣma in the Mahāvyūha of Kauravas
(वेणिकाः कुकुरास् तथा। … भीष्मम् एवाभि-
रक्षन्तु सह सैन्यपुरस्कृताः॥; अव्यू-
हन्त महाव्यूहम्) 6. 47. 7, 9-10.

वेणुप
Veṇupa m. (pl.): Name of a people.
Kṛṣṇa told Karṇa that if he joined
the side of Pāṇḍavas, Veṇupas would be
among those who would lead his procession
(पुरोगमाश् च ते सन्तु … चूचुपा वेणुपास्
तथा) 5. 138. 25.

वेणुमण्डल
Veṇumaṇḍala nt. (sg.): Name of a
Varṣa.
Second among the seven Varṣas of the
Kuśadvīpa which is to the north of the
Jambudvīpa (उत्तरेषु … द्वीपेषु … । …
द्वितीयं वेणुमण्डलम्) 6. 13. 1, 12; for
the characteristics common to all Varṣas
of Kuśadvīpa, see Audbhida2.

