सिराल
Sirāla m. (pl.): Name of a Janapada.
Listed by Saṃjaya among the southern
Janapadas (also called Deśas 6. 10. 68) of
Bhāratavarṣa (अथापरे जनपदा दक्षिणा
 … ) 6. 10. 56, 5; (आदिदायाः सिरालाश् च)
6. 10. 62.

सुकुटि
Sukuṭi m. (?) (pl.): Name of a Jana-
pada.
Listed by Saṃjaya among the northern
Janapadas (also called Deśas 6. 10. 68) of
Bhāratavarṣa (for citation see Sirāla);
(मत्स्याः सुकुट्यः) 6. 10. 38.

सुकुट्ट
Sukuṭṭa m. (pl.): Name of a Jana-
pada and its people.
A. Location: Listed by Saṃjaya
among the northern Janapadas (also called
Deśas 6. 10. 68) of Bhāratavarṣa (अत
ऊर्ध्वं जनपदान् निबोध) 6. 10. 37, 5;
(आदिराष्ट्राः सुकुट्टाश् च) 6. 10. 43.
B.
Epic event: Afraid of Jarāsandha they,
along with many others, took resort in the
west (जरासन्धभयाद् एव प्रतिचीं दिशम्
आश्रिताः॥ … सुस्थराश् च सुकुट्टाश् च) 2.
13. 24-25.

सुकुमार
Sukumāra m. (sg.): Name of a Varṣa.
One of the Varṣas of the Śākadvīpa;
it lay beyond the Jaladhāra mountain
(जलधारात् परो राजन् सुकुमार इति स्मृतः)
6. 12. 23.

सुदर्शन
Sudarśana m., nt. (sg.): Name of a
द्वीप।
A. Its form: Round, like a wheel
(परिमण्डल; चक्रसंस्थित) 6. 6. 12
(Nī. on Bom. Ed. 6. 5. 13: चक्रसम्स्थित
इत्य् अनेन चक्रवत् संस्थितं संस्थानम्
आकारो ऽस्य); surrounded on all sides by
salty ocean (लावणेन समुद्रेण समन्तात्
परिवारितः) 6. 6. 14.
B. Description:
It is rich with wealth and full of crops
(संपन्नधनधान्यवान्) 6. 6. 14; it is
covered with trees full of flowers and fruits
(वृक्षैः पुष्पफलोपेतैः (प्रतिच्छन्नः))
6. 6. 14; it has a variety of plants on all sides
(सर्वौषधिसमावापैः सर्वतः परि-
बृंहितः) 6. 6. 16; covered with waters of
rivers and with mountains looking like
clouds; also covered with towns of different
sizes and with countries which are beauti-
ful (नदीजलप्रतिच्छन्नः पर्वतैश् चाभ्र-
संनिभत्ः।पुरैश् च विविधाकारै रम्यैर्
जनपदैस् तथा) 6. 6. 13.
C. Its
special features: (1) Just as one can see
one's face in a mirror, so can one see the
Sudarśana island in the orb of the moon
(यथा च पुरुषः पश्येद् आदर्शे मुखम्
आत्मनः।एवं सुदर्शनद्वीपो दृश्यते
चन्द्रमण्डले) 6. 6. 15; (2) On its two
parts (?) there is a पिप्पल tree, and on two
parts a large hare (?) (द्विरंशे पिप्पलस्
तत्र द्विरंशे च शशो महान्) 6. 6. 16
(According to Nīlakaṇṭha's interpretation
(which does not appear to be correct) of
6. 8. 18-19 (= Nī. 6. 5. 13) Sudarśana is
another name of Jambūdvīpa: सुदर्शनो
नाम जम्बूवृक्षविशेषस् तन्नाम्नाङ्कितो
ऽयं द्वीपः सुदर्शनद्वीपः। But the
words तस्य नाम्ना in st. 19 refer to
जम्बूवृक्षः of st. 18 and not to the name
सुदर्शन of that tree).

